        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix, roll, bake, 12 to 14 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C fan. Line two baking trays with baking paper. Whisk together the {{plain-flour}}, {{ginger-ground}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, and {{caster-sugar}} in a large bowl. Melt the {{unsalted-butter}} and {{golden-syrup}} together in a small saucepan over low heat, then pour into the dry ingredients and stir until a firm dough forms. Roll into balls of about 12 g each (a rounded teaspoon) and space them 4 cm apart on the trays. Flatten slightly. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes until the surface is cracked and dry. These are ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "snap biscuits",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yu3tg0000fov4z01th88q"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": leave them on the tray for 10 minutes to firm before moving to a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
